            <p><name type="place">Washington</name></p>
            <p>Apr. 5, 1896.</p>
            <p>My dear <name type="person">Mr. Walsh</name></p>
            <p><name type="person">I</name> have no time to write <name type="person">you</name>a letter, but here are some little flowers from <name type="person">Lily</name>â€™s grave that have
                just come to <name type="person">me</name>. <name type="person">I</name> send these to <name type="person">you</name>, for <name type="person">I</name> shall doubtless get more. My correspondent tells me
                that the grave is beautiful now, and well kept.</p>
            <p>I hope <name type="person">you</name> are well and less unhappy than <name type="person">I</name> know <name type="person">you</name> to have been.</p>
            <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
            <p><name type="person">Ambrose Bierce.</name></p>
